hich accounts for about  of the firms revenue citadel securities also executes about  percent of us consolidated volume in equities and  percent of us retail equities volume in  citadel securities expanded its marketmaking offering to interestrate swaps one of the most commonlytraded derivatives according to a report in the march  edition of risk magazine citadel provides quotes to traders in an average time of  seconds compared to  seconds for the next closest market maker the move into derivatives trading aligns with mandatory clearing requirements under the doddfrank act a provision intended to prevent a future lehman brothersstyle collapse citadel securities retail trading platform is headed by jamil nazarali who was named to the  trading technology  by institutional investor in july  citadel hired microsoft coo and former walmart executive b kevin turner to be the ceo of citadel securities in january  turner left citadel and was replaced by the vice chairman of the whole firm peng zhao citadel technologyedit citadel technology established in  is the wholly owned and independently operated affiliate of citadel it offers investment management technology developed internally at citadel to a wide range of firms and funds in  citadel technology announced a partnership with redi the partnership combines citadels order management system oms with redis execution management capabilities ems historyedit foundingedit ken griffin launched his trading career out of his dorm room at harvard university in  with  raised from friends and family as a sophomore he traded convertible bonds and hooked a satellite dish to the roof of his dormitory after graduating with a degree in economics griffin joined chicagobased hedge fund glenwood partners led by hedge fund pioneer and griffin mentor frank meyer in november  griffin founded citadel with meyers backing early historyedit according to a new york times report citadel was started with  million in capital citadel was originally named wellington financial group after its flagship fund the company name was changed to citadel in  within eight years the firm had more than  billion in assets in  citadel started requiring investors to accept terms that restricted their ability to withdraw their capital according to institutional investor when fund longterm capital management collapsed later that year citadels capital lockdown made it a rare buyer as desperate hedge funds unloaded bond inventory the  financial crisisedit during the  financial crisis the firms kensington and wellington funds lost  percent of their value by the end of the year griffin said we were losing hundreds of millions of dollars a week if not more cnbc parked a van in front of citadel waiting to break the story of our demise citadel suspended shareholder redemptions which griffin called one of the most difficult decisions in citadel history griffin later conceded that the firm was overly confident it could weather any financial storm he covered all investor management expenses during that period on january   citadels flagship funds crossed their respective high water marks earning back the losses from  griffin stated we did exactly what we said we would do and we did it the right way the world changed dramatically in  and we adapted our capabilities and resources to successfully compete in this new environment risk managementedit citadels investing approach changed following the  financial crisis according to risk magazine the foundation of citadels success is in large part a result of the risk management ethos the firms risk management philosophy is focused on three main areas risk capital allocation stress exposure and liquidity management citadels risk management center has  monitors displaying more than  instruments being traded within the firms portfolios it is a realtime view of citadel’s risk exposures across its investments and market making operations globally the firm runs  stress tests each day to simulate the impact of potential economic and geopolitical crises or other market dislocation citadel aggregates investment positions on trading screens to calculate more than  doomsday scenarios to assess the potential of risk for the firm in  citadel rated an a grade for risk management in the annual institutional investor hedge fund report card in april  ben s bernanke who was the united states federal reserve chairman for eight years joined citadel as a senior adviser on global economic and financial issues major investmentsedit citadel is known for its many notable investments over the years in  the company acquired large portions of amaranth advisors energy portfolio in  citadel purchased the entire portfolio of rival hedge fund sowood asset management over the course of a weekend negotiation sowood had lost hundreds of millions of dollars and had to liquidate their portfolio to meet margin calls prior to the opening of the market on monday in november  citadel provided a  billion cash infusion to etrade financial taking a nearly  percent stake in the online broker that was ensnared in the home mortgage crisis in a  letter to the etrade board citadel criticized the company for destroying more than  billion in stockholder value for a phenomenal franchise the letter called on etrade to explore a sale of the company in  citadel sold its remaining share in etrade market advocacyedit citadel has played an active role in market structure issues and has advocated for financial legislation in  congress repealed a provision in the glasssteagall act of  that strictly separated banking and trading activities by financial firms griffin called dismantling that law one of the biggest fiascos of all time in the aftermath of the  financial crisis griffin and citadel called for greater transparency in derivatives trading a stance at odds with many other hedge funds and major financial firms the company spoke out against wall street for lobbying to delay the implementation of the doddfrank act griffin has also called for breaking up too big to fail banks and separating their banking and trading activities following the  publication of flash boys by michael lewis who claimed financial markets are rigged by highfrequency traders at the expense of smaller investors griffin became a highprofile defender of todays markets pushing for the transformation from a dealerdominated model to one that is more transparent automated and competitive griffin claimed us equity markets are the fairest most transparent resilient and competitive in the world before the senate banking committee as a part of a series called citadel conversations stephen berger spoke out advocating for fair open and transparent markets officesedit citadel employs more than  individuals globally with its flagship operation located in the citadel center a  million office tower in the heart of downtown chicago the story citadel center office tower opened in  with citadel as its anchor tenant citadel also has offices in new york hong kong san francisco boston dallas london houston greenwich denver shenzen shanghai and toronto philanthropyedit citadel is an active participant in the community by providing educational opportunities and helping children and families with acute medical needs the firm also partners with food banks around the united states for a virtual food drive in  citadels contributions to the greater chicago food depository were the highest from a single corporate donor in that organizations history citadel leads a business plan competition for the national foundation for teaching entrepreneurship mentoring low income high school students in january  citadel partnered with the national museum of mathematics momath to tutor prepare and support math and science students from low income communities recognitionedit citadel has been acknowledged through various awards and accolades in  citadel received a peoples pick award as one of the  great places to work in financial services the firm also ranked among the top  companies to work for according to employee surveys by great places to work in  in  institutional investoralpha magazine gave citadel an a grade and the  ranking among hedge funds worldwide in  citadel was named the best overall hedge fund group in the hedge funds reviews americas award institutional investor named citadel multistrategy hedge fund manager of the year in  and  and institutional hedge fund manager of the year in  see alsoedit kenneth c griffin the quants how a new breed of math whizzes conquered wall street and nearly destroyed it merrill lynch pierce fenner  smith inc v manning a  supreme court case involving naked short selling claims against citadel derivative group and merrill lynch and others referencesedit  a b bit kelly  october  griffins citadel rose in september as hedge funds fell bloomberg retrieved  december    a b c lynne marek  october  why hedgefund operator citadel is becoming a stockbroker crains chicago business retrieved  december    david snider chris howard february   money makers inside the new world of finance and business palgrave macmillan pp – isbn  retrieved july     marek lynne  october  citadel back from the brink crains chicago business retrieved  february    a b hutchins william december   citadel leads the way in financial selfsufficiency financial times retrieved   kolhatkar sheelah  april  opening up the citadel upstart business journal retrieved  february    rosesmith imogen   land of the giants pdf alpha magazine p  retrieved  dead link  allen susie huang wen  july  two new members elected to university of chicago board of trustees u chicago news retrieved  february    a b c copeland rob  august  citadels ken griffin leaves  tumble far behind wall street journal retrieved  october    investment strategies citadel retrieved  february    a b c devasabai kris  october  citadel prepares for swap marketmaking role risknet risk magazine retrieved  july    michael j de la merced january   citadel p